## Quickstart

**You’ll need to have Node 16 or later on your local development machine** (but it’s not required on the server). You can use [fnm](https://github.com/Schniz/fnm) to easily switch Node versions between different projects.

```sh
fnm use
<%= installCommand %>
<%= runCommand %> build
```

## Features

- **Monorepo** - All packages are managed by [Turborepo](https://turborepo.com/).
- **Workspaces** - All packages are managed by [Workspaces](https://docs.npmjs.com/cli/v7/using-npm/workspaces).
- **Changesets** - All packages are managed by [Changesets](https://github.com/changesets/changesets).
- **TypeScript** - All packages are written in [TypeScript](https://www.typescriptlang.org/).
- **ESLint** - All packages are linted by [ESLint](https://eslint.org/).
- **Prettier** - All packages are formatted by [Prettier](https://prettier.io/).
- **Shared UI** - Reusable React components in `packages/ui`, tested with [Vitest](https://vitest.dev/).
- **Web app** - A minimal [Vite](https://vitejs.dev/) + React app in `apps/web` that imports workspace packages.
- **Storybook** - A [Storybook](https://storybook.js.org/) playground in `apps/playground` for component docs.
- **Local Development Environment** - Tooling and configuration to develop shared packages and applications together.

## Pre-packed

### Dev tools

- [TypeScript](https://www.typescriptlang.org/)
- [Turbo](https://turborepo.com/) - A monorepo manager for JavaScript and TypeScript
- [Changesets](https://github.com/changesets/changesets) - A way to manage your versioning and changelogs with a focus on multi-package repositories
- [eslint](https://eslint.org/) - Linting utility for JavaScript and JSX
- [prettier](https://prettier.io/) - Opinionated code formatter
- [Vitest](https://vitest.dev/) - Unit tests for shared packages

## Applications and Packages

- **Web** (`apps/web`) - Vite + React app that consumes `<%= scope%>ui`.
- **Playground** (`apps/playground`) - Storybook for documenting shared components.
- **UI** (`packages/ui`) - Shared React component library.

Need another app (API, extension, Next.js site)? Scaffold it with [create-awesome-node-app](https://www.npmjs.com/package/create-awesome-node-app) and add it under `apps/`.

## Available Scripts

In the project directory, you can run:

| `<%= runCommand %> <script>` | Description                                                                                                             |
| ------------------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `dev`              | Start development servers (`apps/web` and package watchers).                                                            |
| `test`             | Runs unit tests with Vitest (via Turborepo).                                                                            |
| `lint`             | [Lints](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/8503559/what-is-linting) the project for potential errors                    |
| `lint:fix`         | Lints the project and [fixes all correctable errors](http://eslint.org/docs/user-guide/command-line-interface.html#fix) |
| `format`           | Formats the project using [Prettier](https://prettier.io/)                                                              |
| `type-check`       | Runs [TypeScript](https://www.typescriptlang.org/) type checking                                                        |
| `storybook`        | Starts the Storybook playground                                                                                         |
| `build`            | Builds all packages and applications                                                                                    |

